Taiwan Power Co. (Taipower) plans to invest over NT $10 billion in wind power generation over the next decade.
The company aims to install 200 wind power generators with a total capacity of 300,000 kilowatts in coastal regions.
In the US, a defense bill amendment could impact offshore wind projects, including one in Massachusetts.
Meanwhile, Long Island Power Authority intends to build 40 turbines to meet renewable energy targets.
The debate over wind farms continues, with concerns about environmental impact and economic viability.
Offshore wind energy is gaining traction globally, with countries like Denmark leading the way.
